From bf4e2f45deed09354c619c40a27537b842afa90c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Pppery <mapreader@olum.org>
Date: Mon, 26 Jan 2026 15:04:21 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 26/50] Support specifying non-English locales for arcanist

Summary:
via a `locale` config setting and/or a `locale` standard arg.

Part of T16388

(The other part is for Phorge-repo command-line scripts, which needs a separate diff)

Also:

- Fix an old TODO
- Fix a place that calls a nonexistent method
- Document some confusing (and forgotten) lore

Test Plan:
- Install the WMF downstream translations extension
- Run `arc set-config load "[\"translations/src\"]"`
- Run `arc set-config locale fr_FR`
- Run `arc` (with no arguments)
 - See the error message about not choosing a workflow in French
- Run `arc diff` (this is a "legacy workflow" rather than a "toolset workflow" which uses different code. I don't fully understand the difference)
 - See the instructions about creating a diff in French
- Run `arc set-config locale bogus`
- Run a toolset arc command
 - See a warning about an invalid locale, but the command otherwise works.
- Run a legacy arc command (like `arc diff`)
  - See a warning about an invalid locale, but the command otherwise works.
  - See only one warning, not two warnings.
- Run `arc set-config locale ca`
- Run an arc command
 - It works and displays things in Catalan
 - This is listed separately in the test plan because the Catalan locale file is defined downstream whereas the French one is defined upstream and I want to make sure they both work.
- Run `arc help --locale en_US' (a Toolset workflow)
  -  See the command in English (because `--locale` overrides the configured locale)
- Run `arc diff --locale en_US` (a legacy workflow)
 - See the command in English (because `--locale` overrides the configured locale)
- Run `bin/translatewiki export --locale fr_FR`
 - See the error message about missing args in French.

